(97, 3, '2018-12-21 09:19:01', '2018-12-21 09:19:01', '<div>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>1. Introduction.</b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            1.1 These are the Terms and Conditions of Service (the “Terms”) for the travel planning platform available at www.wellplanned365.com (the “Site”), including its sub-domains and its mobile optimized versions, along with any products and services offered thereby. These Terms shall supplement our Privacy Policy, our Cookie Policy and our Copyright Policy, incorporated herein by reference.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            1.2. The Site and the related products and services are proudly provided by the Well Planned 365 Team (hereinafter referred to as “<b>Well Planned</b>”). The terms ‘<b>us</b>’, ‘<b>its</b>’, ‘<b>ours</b>’ and/or ‘<b>we</b>’, as used herein, refer to us, Well Planned and/or our affiliates, assignees, successors and/or brands. As used herein, the terms ‘<b>you</b>’, ‘<b>your</b>’, and/or ‘<b>yourself</b>’ refer to you, a user/visitor/browser of our Site, whether registered under an account or not.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>\r\n                                2. Services Offered.\r\n                            </b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            2.1. If you continue to browse and use Well Planned, you hereby acknowledge and agree to be bound by and under these Terms which, together with our Policy, will govern Well Planned’s relationship with you in relation to the Site, along with any professional social networking services offered thereby (the “<b>Service(s)</b>”).\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            2.2. Our Services encompass a custom travel itinerary planning service, where our platform creates a travel proposal based on your input from our menus. We will request that you select and indicate us several item categories, such as age group of you and your party, destination, preferred type of accommodation, total trip days, vacation type (e.g. sightseeing, play, adventure, night life, shopping, relaxing, nature), proffered transpiration (air, sea, land), types of cuisine proffered, type of restaurant preferred (e.g. fine dining, casual dining, cafes, buffet, fast food).\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            2.3. If you are not sure of a category, we will offer you several suggestions, based on our proprietary, unique travel algorithm. This is one of our main value added propositions for you and your fellow travelers.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>3. Specific Disclaimer.</b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            3.1. Well Planned is not an operator of tours, travel activities, nor is it a provider of tours or activities, a hotel, airline, car company, restaurant, taxi company or transportation company; and Well Planned does not own, sell, resell, furnish, provide, manage and/or control any hospitality, transportation or tour services. Henceforth, Well Planned’s responsibilities are limited to providing a day-by-day travel itinerary for the user’s requested city.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            3.2. For purposes of these Terms, a “Force Majeure Event” shall mean an act of God, act of terrorism, flood, tsunami, strike or other labor condition or dispute, an order or injunction of any court or administrative body or any other act of public authority, severe weather threatening the safety of travelers or a similar contingency or unexpected event, and any such occurrence beyond the reasonable control of Well Planned. Accordingly, Force Majeure Event shall include, but will not be limited to, heavy rain, airport delays, airline delays and poor weather conditions are difficult to predict --yet can cause last-minute disturbances to one’s travelling experience.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            3.3. If a travel package is cancelled, changed or modified, in whole or in part, due to a Force Majeure Event, you will not be entitled to a refund from us. This is under the understanding that we do not provide the actual products and services offered by third parties such as airlines, hotels, car leasing companies and other.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            3.4. While we make a commercially reasonable effort to ensure the information provided is accurate and up-to-date, you as the traveler are ultimately responsible for checking your itinerary and making sure that suggested routes, addresses, opening times, hotel categories, plane tickets and other information is accurate and up to your personal standards.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>\r\n                                4. Account Registration and Security.\r\n                            </b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            4.1. In order to use our Services, you will need to create an account, including all mandatory fields on the registration form. You must provide accurate and complete account information. If you use an email also used on other websites, you must use an original, different password. You agree to keep secret the password chosen upon creating your account and not to communicate it to anybody and, if you lose or disclose it, you must promptly inform us.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            4.2. You are solely responsible for the activity that occurs on your account and for keeping your password secure and confidential, and must notify us immediately of any breach of security or unauthorized use of your account. You will be liable for any and all misuse of your account, including the fraudulent use by a third party, or even the disclosure of your password.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            4.3. Well Planned encourages you to report violations of our Terms. Users undertaking conducts that may constitute a factual –or even alleged– breach of these Terms, including but not limiting, using automated mechanisms to make fraudulent communications, may become subject to immediate account suspension / termination, at our sole and final discretion, without notice and without responsibility.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            4.4. We reserve the right, at our sole and final discretion, to deactivate, freeze, suspend or terminate any account upon any factual or alleged breach of these Terms.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            4.5. You must notify us immediately of any change in your eligibility to use Well Planned, or if you suspect a breach of security or unauthorized use of your account.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            4.6. You acknowledge and agree that we may report any activity that we believe may violate any law to law enforcement, regulators or other relevant third parties, and that any violation of the aforementioned provisions may result in the immediate termination of your access to the Services.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>\r\n                                5. Service Eligibility.\r\n                            </b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            5.1. Well Planned does not provide its Services to persons under the age of eighteen (18). If you are under such age, you may only use them under the direct supervision of your parent or legal guardian.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            5.2. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from persons under the age of thirteen (13). If that becomes the case, we will delete or make permanently inaccessible such user data.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>\r\n                                6. Fees & Payments.\r\n                            </b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            6.1. You must provide us valid and current billing information, and if we detect any chargeback or if any payment is not received by us for any reason from your card or account, you will promptly pay us any and all amounts due to us upon notice.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            6.2. Any failure or inability by us to process any payment hereunder does not relieve you from your payment obligations.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            6.3. We use worldwide accepted third-party payment processors to bill you through a payment account linked to your account. You hereby authorize us the charging of fees through your indicated payment processing account.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            6.4. The processing of payments will be subject to the fees, terms, conditions and privacy policies of such payment processors.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            6.5. Well Planned is not responsible for any and all errors, fees and currency conversions fees by the payment processor, and you should review its terms and policies from time to time, which will govern the provision of services to you.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            6.6. Depending on your place of residence, Well Planned may collect taxes on orders, and you will be able to review them before placing your final order. Tax obligations are not optional, but if you deem that we are charging taxes based on erroneous geographical information of yours, please contact us to solve the matter.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>\r\n                                7. Refund Policy.\r\n                            </b>\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            7.1. If you have a problem with our Services, please contact us as soon as possible. Due to the nature of our Services, we are only able to offer refunds for our service fees if there is a technical issue on our side causing the travel package to be inaccessible on your account. Henceforth, refunds will only be provided at our sole and final discretion, and only for 7 days after purchased orders. Please include a description of the travel package in question, including the reason for your technical query, your name, address, account information and payment details.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            7.2. Refunds for products and services pro